;(Talk to Robin)
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 robin 101.ogg}} '''Robin:''' Finally, you've arrived.
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 acheron 117.ogg}} '''Acheron:''' Let me introduce you to Robin. She woke up from Ena's Dream by her own will, and it's this tough lady who led us here with her song.
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 robin 102.ogg}} '''Robin:''' I woke up for the same reason as all of you. In the dream, I experienced something that could never occur in reality...
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 shaonv 101.ogg}} '''Robin:''' Are we going to lock it up in a cage? I want to see it fly freely in the sky.
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 shaonian 101.ogg}} '''Sunday:''' Without us, this bird would be too fragile to survive on its own. Do you want it to die?
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 shaonv 102.ogg}} '''Robin:''' No, but...
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 shaonian 102.ogg}} '''Sunday:''' ...
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 shaonian 103.ogg}} '''Sunday:''' Then let's take care of it together until it can return to the sky.
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 shaonv 103.ogg}} '''Robin:''' ...Huh?
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 shaonian 104.ogg}} '''Sunday:''' Birds have wings because they're meant to fly. Even if they may crash on the ground one day, they shouldn't be trapped in a cage.
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 shaonian 105.ogg}} '''Sunday:''' Birds belong to the sky, so we should help them return there, right?
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 robin 103.ogg}} '''Robin:''' ...The illusion was so impossibly blissful that I realized it was just a dream.
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 robin 104.ogg}} '''Robin:''' And this is our final hope. Ena's Dream is founded upon the Harmonious Choir, namely everyone's shared wishes. It will only materialize once the aspirations of all beings in Penacony merge as one.
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 robin 105.ogg}} '''Robin:''' At present, it has become impervious due to people's desire to remain slumbering within the dream. And in order to destroy it...
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 robin 106.ogg}} '''Robin:''' We must make everyone in Penacony {{Color|keyword|nobold=1|want to wake up}}.
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 blackswan 147.ogg}} '''Black Swan:''' Now comes the tricky part. How do we do it?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} I'm curious, too.
::I'm curious, too.
::That doesn't sound simple at all...
::Maybe we should just go back to Ena's Dream?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} That doesn't sound simple at all...
::That doesn't sound simple at all...
::Maybe we should just go back to Ena's Dream?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Maybe we should just go back to Ena's Dream?
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 blackswan 148.ogg}} '''Black Swan:''' You want to go back? Unfortunately, human consciousness always gravitates toward reality. Now that you've seen the flaw in the dream, there is no turning back.
:{{A|VO chapter3 25 blackswan 149.ogg}} '''Black Swan:''' Humans' yearning for sweet illusions borders on obsession, leading them to subconsciously resist... the harsh reality.
:{{tx}}
